title: Local Trio Named to All-UMAC Golf Team
text:
Local Trio Named to All-UMAC Golf Team 
By Zach Schneider Local Trio Named to All-UMAC Golf Team October 12, 2015 Updated Oct 12, 2015 at 4:05 PM CDT 
(NNCNOW.com) --- Three men's golfers representing three area colleges have been named to the all-Upper Midwest Athletic Conference (UMAC) team, it was announced on Monday afternoon. 
Northland College junior Evan Lunda was the top area golfer at last weekend's UMAC championships, finishing in fourth place with a three-round total of 227. 
Click here to subscribe to our daily newsletter. 
UW-Superior junior Anton Svensson finished just behind him, firing a score of 232 to finish in sixth place. 
St. Scholastica sophomore Marc Peterson also earned a top 10 finish, shooting a three-day total of 233 to finish tied for seventh place.
